            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Yeah, that whole blog post is pretty much garbage. TL;DR is \"don't be an idiot and use Flask properly\". Just like you shouldn't use `%` interpolation with a DBAPI...\n\n> `<a href='{{ url_for('hello_xss')}}?name={{ name |e}}'>...</a>`\n\nThat's not even secure, since you are supposed to use double quotes for tags with dynamic data. And building the query string manually after `url_for`? Really?\n"
